                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.5151/329: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Philip</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-18T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 18, 1936—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. My telegram No. 56, June 13, 3 [<hi rend="italic">6</hi>] p.m.<note n="43"
                        xml:id="d312fn43">Not printed.</note> Entry of motor vehicles and radios in
                    customs and in transit being facilitated but Board of Exchange Control states
                    that such permits will be furnished only as conditions permit. Indications are
                    that this delay will be a question of months.</p>
                <p>Will request Minister of Foreign Affairs to endeavor to have this delay shortened
                    as much as possible in order that additional frozen credits may be obviated.</p>
                <p>Please inform Department of Commerce.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Philip</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
